  "text": "n is the Shapley operator (2.4) of a finite stochastic game with perfect information, Hoffman and Karp [CITATION_1] have introduced a policy iteration algorithm, which takes the description of the game as the input and returns the eigenvalue λ and an eigenvector u of T , i.e., a solution (λ, u) ∈ R×R n of the ergodic equation T (u) = λe + u. Also, optimal stationary strategies for both players in the mean-payoff game can be derived from the output of the algorithm.",
