      "span_text": "Hoffman and Karp [CITATION_1] have introduced a policy iteration algorithm, which takes the description of the game as the input and returns the eigenvalue λ and an eigenvector u of T , i.e., a solution (λ, u) ∈ R×R n of the ergodic equation T (u) = λe + u."
